POLICE are searching for a five-year-old boy who has gone missing on an island.
Bradley Simpson was last seen in the Norstane area of Lerwick in Shetland at around 4pm today.
He is between three-and-a-half to 4ft tall, of slim build with short cropped fair hair and blue/green eyes.
When last seen he was wearing a dark brown jacket with a hood and a Macmillan charity badge attached.
The little boy was also wearing a red and grey striped jumper with a hood, dark blue jeans and white and blue trainers.
Anyone with information about his whereabouts is urged to contact police on 101.
